caption: Family’s style Thai foods - yummy. I wish the chair can be more comfortable.

Great specials, and overall delicious and interesting menu. We love the snapper special!  They don’t typically have outdoor tables out front; but there IS a covered garden in the back. Semi enclosed for the winter.

on the walk back home from receiving second vaccine shot, picked up dinner ... perfect meal post shot, first day of day light saving, glorious windy sunday late afternoon ... support your local small business.
Cute and authentic! We were only table so its covid safe
I ORDERED Khao Ka Pow.  Vegetable and rice tasted spoiled.  I don't think they use a fresh ingredient.
Very nice and tasty dishes, immediate delivery! We love this place.
The meals and service were beyond our expectations. I truly enjoyed the vibes of this spot. Fantastic restaurant to take my family out for lunch.
Fantastic and yummy food, I loved the ambience this place has, and the staff members were helpful. Will surely come back.

Fantastic Thai Food!! We ordered the homemade pork dumplings (fabulous), crispy pork pad thai (also delicious) and Num Tok Noodle Soup which was sweet and spicy and incredibly flavorful. We recently moved into the neighborhood but this will definitely be our go-to Thai restaurant!
Delish and authentic. Even my 3yr old had the spicy Bangkok Guay Tiao Tom Yum soup and loved it! Wish I had known of this place sooner.  Delivery was quick. Can’t wait to order from here again.
Best delivery I’ve had all quarantine. A+ pork dumplings and sweet sticky rice. Will order again, thank you !

I don’t know how I could miss this Thai place after living in BK for a year. I ordered the boat noodle soup, Tom Yum noodle soup, chicken wings and dumplings and they were all very tasty. I asked for the Spicy level, oh boy it’s really spicy, in a good way! I highly recommend this place, the options you have from this restaurant are unlike the typical (Americanised) Thai restos, which is a sign of authenticity.  This is def one of the best Thai restos I have ever tried in NY. Very reasonably priced as well.

Amazing! Come here if you want home cooked and Authentic Thai food. You can certainly tell this place puts in a lot of extra work to make sure they get the best tasting Thai herbs. I got the spicy eggplant with chicken and my grandmother got the Sweet and sour chicken. The balance between the Thai chilies, ginger, and sauce were perfect. I was completely satisfied! The also serve rice on the side which really helps balance the dish and is delicious to dip in the sauce.
Ahhhmazing Food!
Wow. This is some of the best Thai food I’ve had in NYC. Will definitely be returning
Great food, home cooking flavor affordable prices,  spicy food that can be to spicy for some palates, they also have non spicy foods. Will go back soon.

Ordered takeout from here the other night. Food arrived hot and timely. The chicken in both our dishes was so incredibly dry, it was hardly edible. It was also suprisingly all white meat, no dark meat at all, which made it even more prone to drying. The chicken with rice and bok choy only had 2 or 3 leaves of bock choy and no sauce :( . we were super bummed. Hope to try the place again on a better night.

I told my friends about this place with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are appetizing and the crew is attentive and cooperative. Every time  we eat in this place we enjoy a pleasing evening.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.

Due to the Covid-19 pandemic , I like to go to places with nice outdoor seating.  When I arrived, I was the only person in the backyard, which was great. My friend arrived shortly,  and other patrons but still were 6 feet apart , so I felt comfortable.  Then, a large group came and sat next to our table , literally 1 foot apart. I was not pleased with this.  Also , the drinks taste like cheap liquor . The waitress did not check in with us and the restaurant looked like it hasn't be cleaned all day.  I would not go back .
Amazing food very well priced
Wings have improved. Always better to dine in person
The Khao Soi is a great reminder of Chiang Mai. Their curries are rich and flavorful, and very cold $4 beers for happy hour are perfect for a summer lunch.
Ordered take out during COVID. Food was five stars and I didn’t get COVID. I had some kinda noodle dish and the crab fried rice. You should try this place.
Best Thai in Brooklyn.
Authentic Home Style Thai food. I felt like I was back in Thailand.

Disappointing after reading all the rave reviews. Food was pretty good but service was quite bad. Brought out all our appetizers and entrees at the same time, constantly asking us if we were finished with half the food left, brought the bill while we were still eating. All of which I could easily forget if the food wow'd me as I expected it to. But it felt above average at best.

Tasty, reasonably priced authentic Thai food in a warm and colorful atmosphere. They have dishes you won't find on other menus, like Khao Soi and Issan dishes. I will definitely be going back. Arroy mak!

We love hanging out. Last night we  found this excellent restaurant which friends told us about. We had a lovely evening there with first-rate dishes and  an experienced crew and a great chief cook. We  added this venue in our phone list  and we shall definitely go again very soon. We deeply recommend.
The spot is amazing and spacious, the food was yummy and the prices were very fair. rapidly, efficient service and very attentive waiters. Will definitely recommend this spot.
Best thai food around!
This is one of the best spot when you craved for Thai noodles. So good, so authentic, so satisfying.

Very average experience. Food was typical NYC Thai food (despite the positive reviews). They brought out a Tom yum for some reason (we didn’t order it), and then got annoyed when we said we didn’t order it. Also gave us a mild dish when we asked for spicy. Overall would not recommend, and goes to show that either people have little taste for Thai food or that small restaurants like this worsen in quality as they get more recognition.
Tasty durian sticky rice and nice service. The pork dumplings and fried fish curry didn't wow me though.
Best (and least Americanized) Thai place among the many in the neighborhood. Several regional dishes not commonly seen in American Thai restaurants.

Some really fascinating dishes - not a standard Thai menu. Had a really good spicy noodle dish and an okay fish cup dish (sounds weirder than it is and it was good but not great).  I'd go back but vegetarian options are kinda limited.
Easily the best Thai restaurant in this neck of the woods and definitely some of the best Northern/Isaan thai food in brooklyn
GOOD food and vibe - they even take reservations!
😎  Place

Terribly confused by the reviews. Maybe we got a bad order, but my partner and I agreed the food had little flavor (even the Pad Thai, which is usually difficult to mess up too bad). In addition, the noodles were mush and everything was too oily.
Nadia & Judy are the best hostesses & their environment / vibe is beautiful!

Just found a new favorite Thai spot in Brooklyn.  So many to choose from but this is my go to now. Best crab fried rice I’ve had since I visited Thailand. Their Bamee Poo Moo Dang is a strong recommendation as well.
The larb is heavenly. Get it!

Delicious food, cozy setting, beautiful outdoor garden. All of the food looks as good as it tastes, and is very reasonably priced. For dessert, I recommend the coconut rice & ice cream. I wish I could order that every day.
Some of the best Thai I've had in NYC
Authentic home cooked style Thai food
Friendly, tasty, good!

This is a goldilocks restaurant, not too big not too small and still has an intimate feel to it, just right. The bar in the front is just big enough and the seating in the back is small but not so small that you would feel cramped. They have a happy hour that is a happy day, as in it lasts all day long and consists of $4 beers and $5 wines.

Oh my lord. This place is amazing. Never upsets, I don’t know why it isn’t busier all the time. I recommend the papaya salad with a side of sticky rice, the crab and pork egg noodle dish, and the garlic sautéed pork. It’s really astounding.
Excellent food. Friendly service. Very satisfying.

Like its sister restaurant Mondayoff, the food here never disappoints. So far I've tried the homemade I-San pork sausage, banana leaf cups (hor mok pla), the Thai boat noodle soup (guay tiao num tok), and the chili paste shrimp noodle soup (num prik phow tom yum goong yai); all were delicious. Combine this with great desserts (can't go wrong with their seasonal mango sticky rice) + warm, friendly service = highly recommended for Thai food in Brooklyn.
Delicious as always.
Authentic spicy noodle soup! Delicious!
Family style authentic Thai restaurant. The food come out steaming and full of flavour. Good prices. Little pearl of the neighbourhood.

I was in the area a few days ago and decided to give this place a try. I enjoyed the food, nothing special but good enough to not disappoint. Give them a try. I had a sampler and a type of curry. For the price I'd expect better portions and flavor.
Good Thai, some different dishes and classics.
Great place.

Great place for lunch. They have a lunch special that includes an entree and spring roll. They have indoor and outdoor seating areas. They weren't busy when my friends and I came. Our waitress was attentive to us. It's a cash-only place. The Thai iced tea was good. I enjoyed my entree.
Disappointing if you are vegetarian, but my meat-eating friends love it.
Feels like back in Thailand

semi-intimate dinning, the bar is inviting, the staff are really pleasent. bathroom was pretty clean, even close to closing.  the food was great, get the lemonade tea...thank me later.  the pad thai..pretty dope ranks in the top 35% of pad thais ive had.  if youre tall, make sure to stretch beforehand ...just a little.  they know how to keep their food spicey ( in spite of cooking in gentrified brooklyn )  2nd time there... wont be my last :D
Really good Thai food in a small cozy place. Bring cash!
The food was all really great and reasonably priced. The Khao Suey was very flavorful but the star dish was their guay tiao num tok. The broth flavor was so intense and aromatic.
Great home cooked vibe Thai.

Tod mun pla was spot on, fried watercress was well prepared and flavorful. The five spice pork belly was ok, a little dry, flavor was mostly soy sauce and not as much of the other spices. Service was not the most cheerful. Not rude but not helpful either, a dish was haphazardly left at the table, a good portion not on the table for instance. I don't think they cared I was there. Also the air smells like kitchen and so did my clothes. Look at the duct running through the dining room and you'll see why.
The restaurant looks really normal, even a little bit old, but the foods are amazing!!

This place is a treat! I had a delicious Khao Soi that zapped my head cold away and the absurdly rich toast dessert. Charming servers, sunny bar seats up front, cozy benches and lighting in back and an outdoor patio. Super cute Bangkok aesthetic. Can't wait to come back.
Laid back atmosphere. Food is well made. Cash only
Thai spot in prospect heights. Nothing mind-blowing, but great for the neighborhood. Fairly priced. Cash only.
Best khao soi in Brooklyn
Slightly sketchy location, but amazing thai food! As close to local thai as you get!
i was disappointed apparently they only have mango (for the desserts) in the summertime.
(Translated by Google) thanks  (Original) Dank
Super authentic. Pork blood soup is great for a cold evening.
Lovely Thai restaurant in Prospect Heights. It's cash only and the rice dishes can be a bit salty, but the starters and noodles are delicious. Worth a visit!
So good. Super quick delivery and the friendliest staff!

Popped in just for dessert, but there is no way we arw leaving NYC without eating dinner here. Once we walked in, the delicious aroma made the decision for us that this was going to be our spot for dinner tomorrow.  We ordered the sizzling brownie, which came out quickly and with amazing presentation.  Sitting on the patio is a must. Beautiful decor and vibe, great for an evening after a day at prospect park.
fresh fresh fresh
hey! this is Miriam from the agency saying hi! one of this days I will come over by :)
Best thai in Brooklyn, hands down
Great food and amazing garden.
Delicious, and the "Thai" spicy will make you cry.
Solid Thai food and there isn't a ton in the area. Cash only. I'd eat here again.
The servings are great and so is the food. Atmosphere is cute as well. I had the pad Thai and it was delicious. If you are looking for Thai food and are in the area, this is a must stop.
Super authentic

Given the dearth of good Thai food in Brooklyn, this is a welcome addition. The boat noodles are hands down my favorite dish there so far. Just be prepared for the kitchen's liberal use of chili powder (mild = spicy!)

Nope. Not at all recommended for vegetarians especially. Firstly the smell of the chicken broth fills up the entire room and is a big put off. With only two options in vegetarian, Pad Thai & Veg Spring Rolls, which also weren't upto the mark. Even friends who ate meat were disappointed by their preparations.
Hidden gem. Authentic thai food with a home made feel.
best thai in the hood!
Delicious and on the cheaper side. Excellent establishment. Extremely friendly staff.
This place has some of the most authentic Thai food this side of Bangkok. The staff is super friendly, super kind, and willing to speak Thai with a rookie. Definitely a must eat.
I just ate a life-changing soup. Head on king prawn + bacon + spicy broth. Very cozy atmosphere and friendly service! The waitress recommended the soup and I couldn't be happier.
Amazing flavours and really well served. all plates are spicy, and have very few vegetarian options.
Delicious Thai food, larb was really really spicy.
Best pad ke mow I've ever had.
This place is authentic. Now I know most other Thai restaurants who claim to be authentic are not genuine.
Food was fab.   Flavors are more authentic in your regular Thai restaurant
So so good. Favorite new restaurant hands down. Service was super nice. I had the Bamee Poo Moo Dang and it was outrageous.
Medium spicy was mouth melting ly hot for the blood sausage soup. People were so nice they brought a new bowl for this spice rookie.
It's the best Thai place in New York.

came here for lunch with some friends.  there's a outdoor seating area.  sit there as there is no AC inside.  food was great but one plate did not mention that it was spicy.  my wife ordered it thinking it was regular friend rice.  oh and cash only.
The Best Thai in all of Brooklyn. Very Traditional and the spice level was great. I eat here about once a week.
Casual and delicious. It was pretty spicy, I think that means its authetic Thai food. I usually dislike Americanized Thai food, but this place gets it right. Nice addition to the neighborhood.
The place should be called, Plant NO Love House. The server was unreasonably mean and the service was terrible.
One of the most flavorful pad thai goongs I've had! While the place isn't ideal for vegetarians, it's quaint, authentic, and accommodating. I look forward to my next visit.
Can you say super super authentic Thai food in the heart of BK?? Well, this is it. I don't even want to tell anyone about this place, and keep it all to myself.

I lived in Thailand as a Peace Corps Volunteer and went here last night and was sooo happy. Friendly staff, authentic food, this is the real deal and the first authentic Asian restaurant in the neighborhood.  The only caveat is that the menu is not expansive and with a heavy focus on seafood and pork, so if you eat semi-Kosher or Halal it can be an issue.  But awesome! Go!
Amazing food with incredible flavor... I order something different every time I go and I am never disappointed. Must try Thai
Fresh aromatic ingredients! Super flavorful and unique dishes. The best Thai I have had in Brooklyn so far. Medium is still spicy!
